            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>soy sauce</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>and cook for a further 4 min or until the sauce becomes sticky and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>spicy hoisin lean pork</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
